President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key positions in his administration. John E. Kramer of Florida is nominated to be the Chief Financial Officer of the Department of Transportation and appointed Assistant Secretary (Budget and Programs) at the Department of Transportation. Paul Shmotolokha of Washington is nominated to be First Vice President of the Export-Import Bank of the United States. Roxanne Cabral of Virginia is nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of the Marshall Islands. B. Chad Bungard of Maryland is nominated to be a Member of the Merit Systems Protection Board. The President also intends to nominate the current seven members of the Financial Oversight and Management Board for Puerto Rico to fill out the remainder of their three-year terms.